OL,3,CHygiene poverty keeping kids out of
OL,4,Cthe classroom, leading charity says
OL,6,F"I have had a story of a lady who
OL,7,Fcried when the local foodbank, who we
OL,8,Fgave products to, had laundry products
OL,9,Fas she had been washing her children's
OL,10,Fclothes in water", she said.
OL,12,FAs the cost-of-living crisis
OL,13,Fcontinues, demand for donations is
OL,14,Frising.
OL,16,F"There has been a stark increase in
OL,17,Fthe need. We are having lots of
OL,18,Fcommunication from more schools and
OL,19,Fcommunity projects for us to help
OL,20,Fthem", Eileen continued.
